# ApplyPilot – AI Usage & Architecture Ownership Notes

## Purpose

This document records how AI is intended to be used during the development of ApplyPilot and clarifies ownership of architecture decisions for portfolio and interview purposes.

---

## Guiding Principle

AI is used as an accelerator, reviewer, and implementation assistant.

The project team remains responsible for:

- Architecture decisions
- Domain modeling
- Business rules
- State machine design
- API contracts
- Final technical decisions

AI assistance does not replace ownership of the system.

---

## Architecture & Domain Design

The project team should primarily define:

- Core domain entities
- Entity relationships
- Database schema
- Application state machine
- System boundaries
- API contracts
- Ownership of data flow

AI may be used to:

- Review designs
- Identify gaps
- Suggest improvements
- Challenge assumptions
- Validate consistency

Final approval remains with the project team.

---

## Implementation

AI may assist with:

- Code generation
- Boilerplate
- Tests
- Documentation
- Refactoring
- PR preparation
- Diagram generation

All generated code should be reviewed and understood before acceptance.

---

